<br>
Agghhh!! What does it mean, how does it work ( or not work ), and is it ever worth considering getting one based on such a bonus, or go with base dam/delay at all times ? <br>
<br>
I've been looking at some Sharli*hulfyuck*hurgblech spear , or something like that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It's 13/28, but has 2 poison or disease. <br>
Is this weapon superior or inferior to a simple 10/20 Trak's tooth? Or perhaps stay with Trak's and switch out the 11/22 shaded dagger in odd-hand for something with one of those other bonuses ? <br>
<br>
Thanks to whoever actually knows about this, i've been asking across two servers for a while now, and it seems to be something that i'm not alone in with my ignorance.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarkellraven>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed of Bristlebane</span><br>  Posts: 2035<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/2/03 8:22:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=205.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Somebody please explain these other damage bonuses</span><hr size=1> Elemental damage bonuses are added to the base damage of the weapon if the mob fails it's resist check.  For example:<br>
<br>
Flaming Dirk is an 11 20 weapon with 3 fire damage.  If the creature completely fails its resist check on a given swing, it will behave as a 14 20 weapon on that hit.  If it completely resists, the weapon will be an 11 20.  Partial resists could yield 12 or 13 base damage.  As a general rule, elemental damage should be considered as hitting for about 50% effectiveness, so the flaming dirk will average around 12.5 20.  This gets better against resistance debuffed mobs and low level mobs, and worse against higher level or resistance buffed mobs.<br>
<br>
Bane damage is similar, but it always works completely against a given mob type and always fails completely against other types (so a stonebladed stelleto is 15 28 against summoned mobs and 14 28 against all others because it's 14 28 with 1 bane damage against summoned).<br>
<br>
Clear enough?<br>
<br>
